      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">The College ¶ Dooen, ¶ Mar 7th 1889 ¶ Baron, Sir F. von Mueller KCMG. ¶ My dear Baron,...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">89.03.07</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From William Clarson</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M1, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS found with a specimen of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Cuscuta">Cuscuta</name> tasmanica</seg> (MEL 2245859). MS annotation by M: 'Answ 11/3/89'. Letter not found.</p>
               </note>The College</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Dooen,<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Longerenong Agricultural College, Vic.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Mar 7th 1889</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Baron, Sir F. von Mueller KCMG.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Baron,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I take the liberty of enclosing for your inspection and naming, specimens of three plants</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>No 1. — <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">
                     <name key="Atriplex">Atriplex</name> (? var)</hi>
               </seg> used to be the great fattening plant for stock on the great plains of the Wimmera district<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Vic.</p>
               </note> but it is only to be met with now in isolated or protected spots where stock cannot approach.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>No 2. ?<seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">
                     <name key="Kochia%20pyramidata">Kochia pyramidata</name>
                  </hi>
               </seg> was also a great standby in drought in this region but it has shared the same fate as the <name key="Atriplex">Atriplex</name> having been eaten out by stock and not having a chance of maturing its seed — the penalty Australia is paying for the squatting system, for many valuable plants are nearly extinct on the vast plains once occupied by the sheep and cattle of the squatters.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>No 3 is certainly a <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">
                     <name key="Cuscuta">Cuscuta</name>
                  </hi>
               </seg> or Dodder, and it prevails over portions of the plains which have not been ploughed or cultivated. I do not know whether it would be likely to infest useful plants on cultivated areas but it is not at all partial to any one plant as a host here, as it adheres to fully 20 different genera<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     </seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Cuscuta">Cuscuta</name>
                     </seg> comprises a number of parasitic or hemiparasitic species.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Very faithfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>William Clarson</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Atriplex">Atriplex</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Cuscuta">Cuscuta</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Kochia%20pyramidata">Kochia pyramidata</name>
            </p>
         </div>
